The paper discusses a system for data-parallel, incremental processing and view maintenance over high-rate streams, which suggests that it could belong to the databases (cs.DB) or data structures (cs.DS) categories. Additionally, the paper introduces a new concept called shared arrangements, which could fall under the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) category. The paper also discusses improvements in query response time and resource consumption, which could fall under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. Finally, the paper mentions improvements in performance for business analytics, graph processing, and program analysis, which could fall under the programming languages (cs.PL) category.
